&gt; How to get values of a search query in Parse server ?

[**Query.find**](http://parseplatform.org/Parse-SDK-JS/api/2.7.1/Parse.Query.html#find) will be able to fetch the results of your queries.
As you can have multiples results, the object that you get is an array of elements

so if you want to display the name of all users of your query you&#39;ll have to iterate to display all of your users.

```javascript
const query = new Parse.Query(Parse.User);
query.equalTo(&quot;sexo&quot;, &quot;feminino&quot;);
query
    .find()
    .then(results =&gt; {
        results.forEach(user =&gt; {
            console.log(user.get(&quot;username&quot;))
        });
    })
    .catch(error =&gt; {
        console.log(error);
    });
```

If you want to have examples of queries [**click here**](https://docs.parseplatform.org/js/guide/#basic-queries)

Hope my answer help you &#128522;

