Ok, the problem is that a fully connected layer (`ts.layer.dense`) expect a `tensor1d` as input, as described in this other question: [Why do we flatten the data before we feed it into tensorflow?][1]

So, to do the trick, the tensor must be re-shaped before the fully connected layer, as:

```
                return {
                    value: {
                        xs : ts.reshape(doc.xs, [-1]),
                        ys : doc.ys
                    },
                    done: false
                };
```

Where the `-1` in `ts.reshape(tensor, [-1])`, means to the transformation function flatten the tensor.

For a visual demonstration, here a YouTube video: [CNN Flatten Operation Visualized][2]


  [1]: https://stackoverflow.com/a/44572335/9691361
  [2]: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mFAIBMbACMA

